dolphins' distribution and spatial associations with potential prey
species, including the spatial responses to a capelin stock collapse of
2003-2006 and recovery in 2007-2009. Since dolphin-prey associations may
be scale-dependent, analyses were conducted at two spatial scales: (1)
the habitat scale, by investigating spatial associations between species
distributions averaged across years, and (2) the mesoscale, by
investigating spatial associations within 50 x 50 km grid cells. At the
habitat scale, dolphins overlapped with different prey species in
different parts of their habitat. At the mesoscale, the dolphins were
associated with blue whiting in southern Atlantic waters, while no prey
